{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/format(format:)"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/format(format:)"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"format","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"format","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!) -> "},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The format strings understood by this function are a subset of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" format language as specified by C99.  The "},{"code":"D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"U","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"W","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"conversions are not supported, nor is the "},{"code":"E","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier.  The GNU","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"extensions "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"l"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"P","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are supported, however, as are the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifiers. The Python extension "},{"code":"f","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is also supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In contrast to ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", this function always produces a UTF-8"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string, regardless of the current locale.  Note that the rendering of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"many formats is locale-dependent and may not match the "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"output exactly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following format specifiers are supported:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"a","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the abbreviated weekday name according to the current locale"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"A"},{"text":": the full weekday name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"text":": the abbreviated month name according to the current locale","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"type":"text","text":": the full month name according to the current locale"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the century number (year\/100) as a 2-digit integer (00-99)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"d","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 31)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/e-3m6a4","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 1 to 31);","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"F"},{"type":"text","text":": equivalent to "},{"code":"Y-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"m-"},{"code":"d","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (the ISO 8601 date format)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"g","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the last two digits of the ISO 8601 week-based year as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"decimal number (00-99). This works well with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"G","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the ISO 8601 week-based year as a decimal number. This works","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"well with ","type":"text"},{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"type":"text","text":": equivalent to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H"},{"text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 24-hour clock (range 00 to 23)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"I"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 12-hour clock (range 01 to 12)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"j"},{"text":": the day of the year as a decimal number (range 001 to 366)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"text":": the hour (24-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 0 to 23);","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"l","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour (12-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 1 to 12);"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"m"},{"type":"text","text":": the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 12)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"M"},{"text":": the minute as a decimal number (range 00 to 59)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"f","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the microsecond as a decimal number (range 000000 to 999999)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"type":"text","text":": either ‘AM’ or ‘PM’ according to the given time value, or the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding  strings for the current locale.  Noon is treated as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"‘PM’ and midnight as ‘AM’. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"P","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"type":"text","text":" but lowercase: ‘am’ or ‘pm’ or a corresponding string for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current locale. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"r"},{"text":": the time in a.m. or p.m. notation. Use of this format specifier is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"discouraged, as many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"R"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in 24-hour notation ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"type":"text","text":"M``)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"type":"text","text":": the number of seconds since the Epoch, that is, since 1970-01-01"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"00:00:00 UTC","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"S"},{"text":": the second as a decimal number (range 00 to 60)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"t"},{"type":"text","text":": a tab character"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"T"},{"text":": the time in 24-hour notation with seconds (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"type":"text","text":"M:"},{"code":"S","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard day of the week as a decimal, range 1 to 7,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Monday being 1. This works well with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard week number of the current year as a decimal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"number, range 01 to 53, where week 1 is the first week that has at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"least 4 days in the new year. See ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This works well with ","type":"text"},{"code":"G","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"w"},{"text":": the day of the week as a decimal, range 0 to 6, Sunday being 0.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This is not the ISO 8601 standard format — use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the time","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"y","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the year as a decimal number without the century"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Y"},{"type":"text","text":": the year as a decimal number including the century"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"z"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hhmm"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":":z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hh:mm"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"::z"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC ("},{"code":"+hh:mm:ss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"). This is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"gnulib ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":":::z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC, with ","type":"text"},{"code":":","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to necessary","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"precision (e.g., "},{"code":"-04","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+05:30"},{"type":"text","text":"). This is a gnulib "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extension. Since: 2.38","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone or name or abbreviation","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"``````: a literal ```` character"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some conversion specifications can be modified by preceding the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conversion specifier by one or more modifier characters.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the numeric"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conversions:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"O","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Use alternative numeric symbols, if the current locale supports those."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"type":"text","text":": Pad a numeric result with spaces. This overrides the default padding"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-"},{"text":": Do not pad a numeric result. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the specifier.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"text":": Pad a numeric result with zeros. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the alphabetic conversions:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^"},{"type":"text","text":": Use upper case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extension."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Since: 2.80"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":": Use opposite case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"extension. Since: 2.80"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, when "},{"code":"O","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is used with ","type":"text"},{"code":"B","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"b","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"code":"h","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", it produces the alternative"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"form of a month name. The alternative form should be used when the month"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"name is used without a day number (e.g., standalone). It is required in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"some languages (Baltic, Slavic, Greek, and more) due to their grammatical","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"rules. For other languages there is no difference. ","type":"text"},{"code":"OB","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a GNU and BSD","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"text":" extension expected to be added to the future POSIX specification,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ob"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Oh"},{"text":" are GNU ","type":"text"},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions. Since: 2.56"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since GLib 2.80, when "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"E"},{"type":"text","text":" is used with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Y"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the date is formatted using an alternate era representation specific to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"locale. This is typically used for the Thai solar calendar or Japanese era"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"names, for example."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ec"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using the alternate era representation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EC"},{"type":"text","text":": the name of the era"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ex"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the time, using the alternate era representation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"EX","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the date, using the alternate era representation"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ey"},{"type":"text","text":": the year since the beginning of the era denoted by the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EC"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"specifier","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"EY","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the full alternative year representation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GL